In one short stay, you can enjoy tramping, hunting, mountain-biking, fishing, swimming, surfing and more. If you’re new to the area or don’t want to go it alone, we’re here to help and there are many local businesses who can guide you with these activities.

Bush to Bay Holiday Stays was founded by Erin Dickson and Wendy Moore. Both are locals with valuable knowledge of the area and are Licensed Agents REAA 2008 with experience in real estate sales and property management in the region.

If you’re a property owner and are interested in listing your property with Bush to Bay Holiday Stays, you can contact us through our website.

Bush to Bay Holiday Stays is associated with Harcourts Opotiki.

Kia Ora!
We are Martin Brinck and Adilson Ramalho  the new owners of Appledore Lodge. We can’t tell you how excited we are to take up this wonderful opportunity in the beautiful Bay of Islands and look forward to extending a warm welcome and exceptional experiences to our guests.
Together we share extensive backgrounds in customer-facing roles that promote Aotearoa: Adilson with 20 years of experience in customer-service roles for multinational companies, and Martin, over three decades as a Flight Service Manager with Air New Zealand international.
Like many Kiwi’s, Covid changed our career paths. That said, we decided that we would continue doing what we do best, which is, welcoming people to this piece of paradise we call home.
Going forward the Lodge will be called Te Awa Lodge. We are making incremental upgrades as we go but ultimately we are intent on offering a peaceful respite for discerning guests from Aotearoa and abroad; to rest, recharge and explore the Bay of Islands and wider Northland.
Please check our website for what we offer.
www.teawalodge.co.nz
We wish you all the very best for 2021.

Wow so much so handy.
* 5mins walk from waterfront and Cruise terminal
* Restaurants - all kinds, big and small, Asian and European and everything else.

* Money changers - at least 2 just downstairs

* Communications - Spark & 2 deg.

You are right in the middle of everything in the city. Feel the buzz and then return to your quiet St
host_about:
A traveler myself I love the ease of staying in others homes/apartments and enjoying a more warm, personal and local experience when traveling. I also always appreciate a property that is thoughtfully equipped with hosts who understand travelers need and are available and very happy to respond and accommodate their guest's needs. Let me provide this for you.

This year I traveled to magical Antarctica (bucket list tick and so much more.) Highly recommend. Also to China (Panda bucket list tick) along with spending 6 weeks in Songdo Sth Korea (cat sitting) and a month in Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. 

Every year I travel during NZ winter to cat sit and have done this for several years including to China and France. This gives me the opportunity to live and experience the area like a local, which I love. 

Walking (fitbit fan) and dancing are my exercise - ballroom, ceroc, rock'n'roll, latin. Come join me, I dance several nights a week. It's a wonderful way to socialize and exercise. 

Being in walking distance of the centre of Auckland city, (our almost 'most livable city in the world') I attend many events - film, theatre, festivals, etc. Its all on my doorstep and I take advantage of it. Life is for living. I am loving living my life.

I invite you to experience all there is on offer in Auckland and to warmly welcome you to the Studio.

description: Our home is located 1 hour 45 minutes drive north of Auckland Airport, at the popular Mangawhai beach.  The house is modern, with fresh, modern furnishings. neighborhood_overview: The surf beach and estuary is a short walk down the hill from the house (rather longer back up!).
